owed with the group law of addition of Witt vectors. Our results also give a\ngeometric characterization of $G(\\pi^{n+1}R)$ which is the subgroup of points\nof $G(R)$ that reduces to identity under the modulo $\\pi^{n+1}$ map.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 24 Apr 2022 11:47:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 5 Dec 2022 10:43:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 29 Dec 2022 02:55:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-02"}
